## Stage 6: Post-Mortem and Archival

### Prompt 6.1 — Research Track Summary

```
Compile the final research track report for {TRACK_ID}.

TRACK SUMMARY:
  Economic thesis:         {ECONOMIC_THESIS}
  Search space size:       |S| = __
  Effective dimensionality: M_eff = __
  Discovery candidates:    |C| = __
  Confirmed signals:       |R| = __
  Replicated signals:      |R_rep| = __
  Cross-replicated:        [yes/no/pending] in universes: __

For each signal that reached confirmation (whether it passed or not):
  - One-line description
  - Train IC → Holdout IC → Live IC (if available)
  - Final status: [confirmed + replicated / confirmed + pending /
                   confirmed + failed_replication / failed_confirmation /
                   failed_discovery]
  - Key diagnostic: the single most informative visual
    (quantile spread heatmap or IC time series)

LESSONS LEARNED:
  - What did the pre-exploratory EDA reveal that informed the search?
  - Were any screening-stage signals surprisingly strong or weak?
  - Did the multiplicity adjustment change the outcome
    (i.e., signals that passed raw but failed adjusted)?
  - What was the confirmation rate |R|/|C| and how does it compare
    to the base rate for this type of signal?
  - If the track failed: at which stage? What would you do differently?

REUSABLE ARTIFACTS:
  - Data quality report (Stage 0)
  - Dependence structure / M_eff estimate (Stage 1)
  - Signal decay curves (Stage 2)
  - Gate contracts (Stage 3)
  These feed into future research tracks and should be versioned.

Archive the complete track: data partitions, gate contracts,
all diagnostic visuals, all decisions, all code.
The archive must be sufficient for a third party to reproduce
every gate decision from raw data.
```

