## Appendix A: Gate Contract Template

```yaml
gate:
  id: "{TRACK_ID}_{GATE_NAME}"
  stage: "{discovery | confirmation | replication | cross_replication}"
  version: 1
  created: "{ISO_DATE}"
  frozen: true

data:
  partition: "{train | holdout | live}"
  date_range: ["{start}", "{end}"]
  universe: "{IG | HY | EM | ...}"
  min_cross_section: {N_min}

test:
  estimator: "spearman_ic"
  null_hypothesis: "rho_s <= {FLOOR}"
  alternative: "rho_s > {FLOOR}"
  sidedness: "one-sided"
  method: "stationary_block_bootstrap"
  block_length: {BLOCK_LEN}
  n_bootstrap: {N_BOOT}

multiplicity:
  n_candidates: {|C|}
  m_effective: {M_eff}
  rdf_multiplier: {RDF_MULT}
  method: "{BH | BY | Holm | Meff-Bonferroni}"
  target_rate: {FDR or FWER target}
  rate_type: "{FDR | FWER}"

decisions:
  reject_action: "{proceed_to_next_gate | deploy | ...}"
  fail_action: "{archive | flag_for_review | ...}"

outputs:
  rejection_set: []  # populated after execution
  diagnostics: []    # paths to visual artifacts
  hash: ""           # SHA-256 of this contract before execution
```

## Appendix B: Visualisation Priority Ranking

For each stage, the single most important visual:

| Stage | Primary Visual | What It Answers |
|-------|---------------|-----------------|
| 0. Data audit | Missingness heatmap (clustered) | Is the data's absence structure informative? |
| 1. Pre-EDA | Signal dependence clustermap + scree | How many independent things am I actually testing? |
| 2. Discovery | Quantile spread return heatmap | Is the signal monotonic and stable over time? |
| 3. Confirmation | Train vs holdout quantile heatmap (side-by-side) | Does the pattern survive out-of-sample? |
| 4. Replication | IC time series with OBF spending boundaries | Is the signal persisting in live data? |
| 5. Cross-replication | Posterior density with prior overlay | How much did the new universe update our belief? |
| 6. Post-mortem | Funnel plot: all |S| raw p-values vs effect size | Publication bias check — does the funnel look symmetric? |

## Appendix C: Automation Checklist

Before declaring the pipeline automatable, verify each criterion:

```
[ ] Every gate has a YAML contract frozen before execution
[ ] Data partitions are enforced architecturally (not by convention)
[ ] The candidate set C is hashed and immutable after discovery
[ ] The multiplicity method is specified before seeing holdout data
[ ] The replication spending function is specified before live monitoring begins
[ ] Every gate produces: (1) a decision, (2) diagnostics, (3) a hash
[ ] No gate's decision depends on human interpretation of a visual
[ ] Visuals are attached to gates as artifacts, not used for decisions
[ ] The full pipeline is reproducible from raw data + gate contracts
[ ] All code is versioned alongside the gate contracts
```
